T1  - An Investigation of the Relationship Between Unemployment and Absenteeism: A Multi-Level Approach
AU  - Markham, Steven E.
Y1  - 1985/03/01
PY  - 1985
DA  - 1985/03/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256071
DO  - 10.5465/256071
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 228
EP  - 234
VL  - 28
IS  - 1
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article discusses research pertaining to the relationship between unemployment and absenteeism at the national level, the regional level, and/or the organizational level. Data on monthly absenteeism rates from 1976 to 1982 were collected from the U.S. Bureau of National Affairs. The results revealed a significant relationship between absenteeism and unemployment. It has found that the absenteeism rate for the organizations included in the study was closely associated with the national unemployment rate and was not significantly associated with the local rate.
AB  - The article discusses research pertaining to the relationship between unemployment and absenteeism at the national level, the regional level, and/or the organizational level. Data on monthly absenteeism rates from 1976 to 1982 were collected from the U.S. Bureau of National Affairs. The results revealed a significant relationship between absenteeism and unemployment. It has found that the absenteeism rate for the organizations included in the study was closely associated with the national unemployment rate and was not significantly associated with the local rate.
